Purpose

Examining Obstructive and Irritative categories (sub-catagories of LUTS) with respect to the urinary microbiome. Also adding the new diabetes categories (08/01/23 from MrOS_SAS_glucose.RMD)

Samples 500 morning, second voided urine specimens that were collected in sterile containers and frozen as part of the MrOS study were obtained with associated clinical information. Bacterial DNA was extracted and the 16S rRNA amplicon was sequenced with Illumina MiSeq. Sequences were processed with DADA2 and analyzed in R. LUTS severity was classified with American Urologic Association Symptom Index ( 0 -7 none/mild; 8-35 moderate/severe)

LUTS-Subanalysis

LUTS categories -

According to AUA (american urology assoc), scores for each symptom go from 0 > 5; 0 = never, 5 = almost always

  1. Over the past month, how often have you had the feeling of not completely emptying your bladder after you finished urinating? PSEMPTY
  2. Over the past month, how often have you had to urinate again less than 2 hours after you finished urinating? PSAGAIN
  3. Over the past month, how often have you found that you stopped and started again several times when you urinated? PSSTOP
  4. Over the past month, how often have you found it hard to hold your urine? PSPOST
  5. Over the past month, how often have you had a weak urine stream? PSWEAK
  6. Over the past month, how often have you had to push or strain to begin urination? PSPUSH
  7. Over the past month, have you had to get up to urinate during the night? Give a score to the number of times. PSUP

ps_g <- tax_glom(ps, "Genus")
ps_g <- subset_taxa(ps_g, taxa_sums(ps_g) > 0)

ps_p <- subset_taxa(ps_p, taxa_sums(ps_p) > 0)

ps_p_n  <- transform_sample_counts(ps_p, function(x) 100* x/sum(x))
# melt to a data frame
mdf <- ps_p_n %>% 
          psmelt()

## to avoid conflicts with special phyloseq plot attribute names.
mdf %>% 
  filter(Phylum %in% c("Firmicutes", "Proteobacteria", "Actinobacteria", "Bacteroidetes")) %>% 
  ggplot(., aes(x = LUTS_cat, y = Abundance)) + 
  facet_wrap(~Phylum, nrow = 1) + 
  geom_boxplot() +
  xlab("LUTS") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(size = 10)) +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_text(size=10))

color_dfs <- create_color_dfs(mdf, group_level = "Phylum")
color_dfs <- reorder_samples_by(color_dfs$mdf,color_dfs$cdf, order_tax = "Firmicutes")

# fix mdf
color_dfs$mdf$group <- str_replace(color_dfs$mdf$group, "-Unknown", "")

color_dfs$mdf$group <- factor(color_dfs$mdf$group, levels = c("Other", "Bacteroidetes", "Actinobacteria", "Proteobacteria", "Firmicutes"))

# fix cdf
color_dfs$cdf$group <- str_replace(color_dfs$cdf$group, "-Unknown", "")
color_dfs$cdf$group <- factor(color_dfs$cdf$group, levels = c("Other", "Bacteroidetes", "Actinobacteria", "Proteobacteria", "Firmicutes"))


plot_g <- plot_microshades(color_dfs$mdf,color_dfs$cdf, group_label = "Phylum")

There are some significant findings here. Namely, that there is an interaction between Obstructive symptoms and BMI for pielou and Shannon index. You see similar significant findings for Obstructive symptoms and age, however when you put all three terms together, its not longer significant. Also interesting that both Shannon and pielou heavily weight the evennness of a community.

Obs vs Irr vs Both (sub_LUTS)

meta_ps <- meta_ps %>% 
  mutate(sub_LUTS = case_when(
    PS_Obstructive > 0 & PS_Irritative == 0 ~ "Obstructive",
    PS_Irritative > 0 & PS_Obstructive == 0 ~ "Irritative",
    PS_Irritative > 0 & PS_Obstructive > 0 ~ "Both",
    PS_Irritative == 0 & PS_Obstructive == 0 ~ "None"
))


temp <- as.data.frame(table(meta_ps$sub_LUTS))
temp <- temp %>% mutate(count = (Freq/sum(Freq)*100))
temp$Symptom <- temp$Var1
temp$Symptom <- factor(temp$Symptom, levels = c("None", "Obstructive", "Irritative", "Both"))

pchart <- ggplot(temp, aes(x = "", y = count, fill = Symptom)) + geom_bar(stat = "identity")
pchart_fin <- pchart + coord_polar("y", start=0) + scale_fill_manual(values = c("#8E4D63","#E3C565","#90AFC5", "#b4d3b2")) + theme_void()

ps_n <- transform_sample_counts(ps,function(x) 100* x/sum(x))
ps_n_phy <- tax_glom(ps_n, "Phylum")
ps_melt <- psmelt(ps_n_phy)
## Warning in psmelt(ps_n_phy): The sample variables: 
## Sample
##  have been renamed to: 
## sample_Sample
## to avoid conflicts with special phyloseq plot attribute names.
summary_phylum <- ps_melt %>%
        group_by(Phylum, Obs_group) %>%
        summarise(rank_abundance = sum(Abundance), mean_abundance = mean(Abundance), median_abundance = median(Abundance), min_abundance = min(Abundance), max_abundance = max(Abundance)) %>%
        arrange(desc(rank_abundance)) %>%
        mutate(order = row_number()) %>%
        ungroup()
